data.name: Elite Doll Neural Custom Gift Box
data.introduction: The custom gift box contains Neural Archives of Elite Dolls, specially prepared by the surrogate. Upon opening, you can choose and obtain 1 Elite Doll's Neural Archive. Available options include: Vepley, Peritya, Sabrina, Tololo, and Qiongjiu.

data.name: Standard Doll Neural Custom Gift Box
data.introduction: The custom gift box contains Neural Archives of Standard Dolls, specially prepared by the surrogate. Upon opening, you can choose and obtain 1 Standard Doll's Neural Archive. Available options include: Groza, Krolik, Nemesis, Colphne, Sharkry, Cheeta, Nagant, Ksenia, and Littara.

data.name: Elite Weapon Neural Custom Gift Box
data.introduction: The custom gift box contains Elite Weapons, specially prepared by the surrogate. Upon opening, you can choose and obtain 1 Elite Weapon. Available options include: Heart Seeker, Optical Illusion, Planeta, Golden Melody, Samosek, and Mezzaluna.

data.name: Standard Weapon Neural Custom Gift Box
data.introduction: The custom gift box contains Standard Weapons, specially prepared by the surrogate. Upon opening, you can choose and obtain 1 Standard Weapon. Available options include: OTs-14, .380 Curva, .50 Nemesis, Hare, Vepr-12, Pecheneg-SP, Robinson Modular Rifle, MP7H1, Model Alpha, QBZ-191, Sportivo Calibro 12, Nagant M1895, Three-line Rifle M1891, Stechkin, and Model ARM.

data.name: Elite Neural Pre-storage Gift Box [Discarded]
data.introduction: The gift box containing random Elite Doll Neural Archives, a surprise specially prepared by the surrogate. After opening it, you can get the Neural archive of a random Elite Doll. Available options include: Vepley, Peritya, Sabrina, Tololo, and Qiongjiu.

data.name: Standard Neural Gift Box [Abandoned]
data.introduction: The gift box containing random Standard Doll Neural Archives, a surprise specially prepared by the surrogate. After opening it, you can get the Neural archive of a random Standard Doll. Available options include: Groza, Krolik, Nemesis, Colphne, Sharkry, and Cheeta.

data.name: Elite Weapon Pre-Storage Gift Box [Discarded]
data.introduction: The custom gift box contains random Elite Weapons, a surprise specially prepared by the surrogate. Upon opening, you can choose and obtain 1 Elite Weapon. Available options include: Heart Seeker, Optical Illusion, Planeta, Golden Melody, and Mezzaluna.

data.name: Standard Weapon Pre-Storage Gift Box [Discarded]
data.introduction: The custom gift box contains Standard Weapons, a surprise specially prepared by the surrogate. Upon opening, you can choose and obtain 1 Standard Weapon. Available options include: OTs-14, .380 Curva, .50 Nemesis, Hare, Vepr-12, Pecheneg-SP, Robinson Modular Rifle, MP7H1, Model Alpha, QBZ-191, and Sportivo Calibro 12.

data.name: Monthly Crystal Contract
data.introduction: A stable contract, suitable for bounty hunters looking for short-term profits. The contract takes effect from the date of purchase and is valid for 1 month. During the validity period, 80 Collapse Pieces can be obtained daily.

data.name: Monthly Incremental Contract
data.introduction:
A contract for sale, providing network service. Once confirmed, the contract allows for modification of simulation data through certain technical means. Bounty hunters seeking to enhance material acquisition efficiency may consider purchasing it.
The contract takes effect from the day of purchase and is valid for one month. During the validity period, the number of additional Standardizing Sync drops and Rewinds will increase daily.

data.name: Hunter's Path Certification
data.introduction: A hardware device that stores digital certifications for specific routes. Hunter's Path routes can be loaded into Elmo's navigation system using this device. After use, the current Hunter's Path can be unlocked in the Voyage Journalism.

data.name: Broker's Path Certification
data.introduction: A hardware device that stores the digital certification of a specific route. The Broker's Path can be loaded into Elmo's navigation system using this device. After use, the current Broker's Path can be unlocked in the Voyage Journalism.

data.name: Re-Evaluation
data.introduction: A hardware device that stores route re-planning authorization, which can be used to re-plan the Hunter's Path and load the re-planned route into Elmo's Navigation system. After use, the unlocked current Hunter's Path can be upgraded to the current Broker's Path in the Voyage Journalism.

data.name: Surplus Goods Crate
Surplus Goods Crate
Journey Guardian Custom Gift Box
data.introduction: "The contamination zones are hazardous, so be prepared!" After opening it, you can choose and obtain 1 elite weapon. The optional weapons include [Classified Manuscript, Papa-Figo, Arcana, Guerno, Crowned Jackalope, Mjölnir, Expeditionary Pigeon].

data.name: Perfect Hunter Skin Crate
data.introduction:
An honorary gift from B.R.I.E.F., filled with various weapon skins to celebrate the birth of a new rookie in the contamination zone.
You can unlock the Phantom Game series of skins for 7 weapons upon opening.

data.name: Daily Free Gift Pack
data.introduction: Receive a free daily gift pack just by logging in. This pack may contain various rewards such as Access Permissions and Collapse Pieces. Login for a total of 21 days to guarantee an Access Permission ×1; 42 days to obtain a Basic Info Core ×1. This will reset after reaching this threshold.

data.name: Elite Doll Neural Custom Gift Box
data.introduction: This custom gift box contains Neural Archives of Elite Dolls, specially prepared by the Agent of the underground brokers. Upon opening, you can choose and obtain 1 Elite Doll's Neural Archives. Available options include: Vepley, Peritya, Sabrina, Tololo, Qiongjiu and Mosin-Nagant.

data.introduction: After opening, you will acquire a precise grade rarity attachment from the specified set combinations.

data.name: Frosted Glass
data.introduction: One of the sources of environmental information in the B.R.I.E.F. contaminated area. Artificial glass fragments that have been affected by Collapse radiation for a long time have transformed into glass-like crystals. The scraping of the Collapse storm has given it different shapes and colors. It can make carrier cards in analysis machines and is one of the most basic raw materials. It will be recycled after the current Boundary Chronicle project is completed.

data.name: Carbon Black Glass
data.introduction: One of the sources of environmental information in the B.R.I.E.F. contaminated area. After being affected by Collapse radiation for a long time, artificial glass mixed with a large amount of impurities reacts with each other to form glass-like crystals. Losing the transparency of glass, the chaotic gray-black color makes this type of crystal look more like metal or mineral. It can make carrier cards in analysis machines and is one of the most basic raw materials. It will be recycled after the current Boundary Chronicle project is completed.

data.name: Solid-State Glass
data.introduction: One of the sources of environmental information about the B.R.I.E.F. contaminated area is glass fragments scraped by the Collapse Storm, which re-forms into glass-like crystals after the solid-phase reaction caused by the long-term impact of the Collapse Radiation. They often appear in the gaps where debris quickly accumulates, and the shape is irregular. They are one of the most basic raw materials and can be used to make carrier cards in analytical machines. After the current Boundary Chronicle project is completed, they will be recycled.

data.name: Mixed Quartz
data.introduction: A mineral with high hardness belongs to quartzite, but due to high impurity content, it has lost the inherent commercial value of quartz. It can be combined with glass-like crystals in the analysis machine to make directional carrier cards. It will be recycled after the current Border Chronicle Project is completed.

data.name: Steel Shingle
data.introduction: Craft material fragments were widely used as a building material in the early years. It can be combined with glass-like crystals in the analysis machine to craft directional carrier cards. It will be recycled after the current Border Chronicle project is completed.

data.name: Black Ore Fragments
data.introduction: The ferrous metal ores have evolved into a new type of mineral under the influence of Collapse radiation. It is no longer possible to extract ferrous metals as in the past. They have lost their activity and have become very stable. They can be combined with glass-like crystals in the analysis machine to produce directional carrier cards. They will be recovered after the current Boundary Chronicle Project is completed.

data.name: Copolymer Core
data.introduction: It's probably a mechanical product from the early years. Under the influence of the Collapse Storm, the metal parts were covered with multiple layers of hard copolymer shells, and the interior was also eroded by the Collapse Particles, making it impossible to trace its previous function and form. It can be combined with glass-like crystals in the analysis machine to make a location-oriented carrier card. It will be collected after the current Boundary Chronicle Project is completed.

data.name: Exotic Alloy
data.introduction: Formed mainly by amorphous metals affected by collapse radiation, with a higher melting point, they can still quickly transform between solid and liquid. They can be combined with glass-like crystals in the analysis machine to make position-oriented carrier cards. They will be recovered after the current Boundary Chronicle project is completed.

data.name: Iridescent Crystal Cluster
data.introduction: The crystal clusters with apparent play-of-color effects are of unknown origin. Some researchers have inferred from their structure that these crystal clusters result from abnormal changes during the formation of Collapse Crystals and do not store Collapse Particles themselves. However, in a radiation environment, their properties are very stable. They can be combined with glass-like crystals in the analysis machine to make position-oriented carrier cards. They will be recovered after the completion of the current Boundary Chronicle Project.

data.name: Color-Shift Rock
data.introduction: Originally, the stone was covered with a large number of moss plants. After the atomic explosion, Collapse radiation spread over a large area, causing the plants to die, but the decayed substances produced by the death of some plants accidentally penetrated into the rock and were preserved. This effect is similar to dyeing, so it is named 'Color Shift'. It can be combined with glass-like crystals in the analysis machine to make functional directional carrier cards. These will be recovered after the current Border Chronicle project is completed.

data.name: Silicon Carbide Composite
data.introduction: After years of impact from Collapse particles and scraping from collapse storms, a silicon carbide composite was formed, which can only be seen in legends. It is one of the materials used to make carrier cards that acquire specific "specific functional type" signals.

data.name: Polyethylene Crystallization
data.introduction: After years of impact from Collapse particles and the scraping of collapse storms, a type of frosted glass that can only be seen in legends has been formed. It is one of the materials used to make carrier cards that obtain specific "specific functional type" signals.

data.name: Dark Tinted Glass Tower
data.introduction: Initially, it was various artificial glass fragments. After the survey area was abandoned, these glass fragments were affected by years of collapse particles and scraped by collapse storms. They eventually formed into dark sand glass towers that should not appear in this world and were called god-level. It has a tiny bonus for making carrier cards that obtain specific 'perfect weapon attachment' signals and is also one of the materials.

data.name: Glass Tower of Glazed Sand
data.introduction: Initially, it was a variety of gravitational polymers. After the survey area was abandoned, these glass fragments were influenced by years of collapse particles and scraped by collapse storms, eventually forming a god-level glazed sand glass tower that should not appear in this world. It has a significant bonus for making carrier cards that obtain specific 'perfect weapon attachment' signals and is also one of the materials.

data.name: Radiant Colored Sand Glass Tower
data.introduction: Initially, it was various dark matter crystals. After the survey area was abandoned, these glass fragments were influenced by Collapse particles over the years and worn down by Collapse storms. Eventually, they formed into a god-level shining sand glass tower that shouldn't exist in this world. It provides a massive bonus for making carrier cards that obtain specific 'perfect weapon attachment' signals and is also one of the materials.

data.name: Coffee Beans
data.introduction: Deeply roasted coffee beans with a smoky aroma. They can be used to complete tasting orders in Creative Tasting events.

data.name: Black Tea
data.introduction: Tea leaves roasted at high temperatures emit a subtle fragrance, can be used to complete tasting orders in Creative Tasting events.

data.name: Cloudberry
data.introduction: Fresh, plump, lovely fruit with the color of the sun. It can be used to complete tasting orders in Creative Tasting events.

data.name: Black Radish
data.introduction: Black radish, Nature's certified black cut white. It can be used to complete tasting orders in Creative Tasting events.

data.name: Cilantro
data.introduction:
A verdant edible plant with mixed reviews.
It can be used to complete tasting orders in Creative Tasting events.

data.name: "Zucchero" Bonus Pack
data.introduction: This is a super-value product in the Zucchero merch. It can only be exchanged three times. You will earn it if you exchange it! After opening it, you can get Collapse piece ×100.

data.name: Silver Coins
data.introduction: Proof of completing the warm-up challenge! It can also be used to scratch lottery tickets. It can be used to submit and receive rewards in Accompany Preparation.

data.name: Action Key
data.introduction: Items for safe access to the database: the more you take, the further you can go! It can be used to purchase defense commands and occupy map grids in Dynamic Defense. These Items will be cleared at the end of the Event.

data.name: Lion's Mane Award
data.introduction: Not only is it a symbol of victory, but it is also recognition from Lenna! It can be used to draw rewards from the surprise data pool.

data.name: Risk Assessment
data.introduction: Even if the surface is calm, don't forget to pay attention to the hidden reefs. It can be used to draw rewards in Pattern Tracing.

data.name: Setting Traps
data.introduction: Give the enemy a blow to the head! It can be used to draw rewards in Pattern Tracing.

data.name: Behavioral Analysis
data.introduction: Details determine success or failure, and every action has its motivation. It can be used to extract rewards in Pattern Tracing.

data.name: Intrusion Investigation
data.introduction: The evidence is solid, and the next step is to catch the criminal! It can be used to draw rewards in Pattern Tracing.

data.name: Spatial Deception
data.introduction: How can you call it cheating to defend against intrusion? It can be used to draw rewards in Pattern Tracing.

data.name: Supply Stamp
data.introduction: Supplies are in short supply; collect them with your stamp! It can be used to redeem rewards in Backstage Supply.

data.name: Starring Voucher
data.introduction: Now, it's time for the protagonist to appear! It can be used to participate in the battles in challenge mode and auto battles.

data.name: Delegated Points
data.introduction: Please don't forget the bounty hunter work, Commander. The economy of Elmo depends on you! It can be used to get rewards in special commissions.
data.description: 降雨版本任务进度材料

data.name: Sweetheart Voucher
data.introduction: A unique gift voucher given to kind hunters, exuding the sweet aroma of excessive caramel. If you quietly give it to Makiatto, you may see her blushing expression. It can be used to exchange rewards in the Sweetheart Shop.

data.name: Fantasy Point
data.introduction: Stage~raise the purple smoke and let's complete the mission of protecting the store anniversary♥ It can be used to obtain rewards in the Rhapsody Commission.
data.description: 玛绮朵版本任务进度材料

data.name: Obsolete Module
data.introduction:

Can be used to redeem rewards in the Trade Zone - Part I.

data.introduction:

Can be used to redeem rewards in the Trade Zone - Part II.
data.description: 索米版本任务进度材料

data.name: Supplies

Can be utilized in Environmental Cleanups.

A forgotten energy storage unit, clean it up and it can still be used.
Using this will restore power.

data.introduction:
An old repair kit that still has some use.
Using this will restore Doll HP.

A powerful little helper during inspections.
Using this allows you to instantly kill an enemy unit without engaging in combat.

data.introduction:
A practical little gadget for inspections. Definitely worth it.
Using this grants a special buff. (Obtaining this module will not trigger any encounters.)

data.name: Supplies
data.introduction: Investigation supply points expended during Wilderness Investigation

data.name: Gifts of Yore

Somewhat aged supply crates. Their mottled exteriors speak of this land's glory and decline.
Grants resources when used.

data.introduction:
A repair kit left behind by a previous explorer. Someone has clearly rummaged through it, but it is otherwise untouched.
Restores Doll HP when used.

data.name: Hand-Drawn Map
data.introduction:
A page from a notebook left by a previous explorer. The art style is most unique. So THAT's where the entrance is...
Opens the next exploration area when used.

data.name: Modular Mortar
data.introduction:
Heavy firepower left behind by a previous explorer, which they could not take away with them. A small quantity of mortar bombs are scattered around it. Say it loud, say it proud: 333!
Instantly destroys an enemy unit without the need for a battle when used.

data.name: Composite Chip
data.introduction:
An old chip that contains data on the area. It can help out during investigations. 
Upon use, it grants a special buff. (Obtaining this item does not trigger encounters.)

data.name: Halting Voucher
data.introduction:

Can be used to attempt Hard Mode stages. Gain 3 tickets during each day of the event. 
Up to 6 can be held at any one time.
data.description: 海外玻璃岛版本主题活动门票

3 vouchers are restored per day while the event of running. Your maximum capacity is 6 tickets.
